               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 2 items (a-b)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of works on eschatology and ethics. Volume not dated. Scribal nastaʿlīq by same hand throughout. Limited annotations in margins. Stamped foliation. Lacking original binding. Binding damaged (torn combed marbled paper on detached pasteboards with leather edging, missing spine), labelled. Additional loose folded paper wrapper (detached sheet from EIC legal collection, mentioning Act XXVI of 1850), watermarked (<orgName>[SA]UNDERS &amp; CO</orgName> 1849), torn, creased, and stained. Folios unbound, detached from boards; wormholes, later repairs. Condition fragile. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1017-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="21v">ff. 1v-21v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise, conventionally entitled <title>Āghāz va anjām</title>, on  Shīʿī eschatology, covering the resurrection, last judgement, and scenarios for subsequent existence by <persName key="person_12392936" role="aut">Nāṣir al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad ibn Ḥasan al-Ṭūsī</persName> (d. 672/1273-4). 

                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into 20 sections termed faṣl listed in the introduction. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_12392936">Nāṣir al-Dīn al-Ṭūsī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_12392936">ناصر طوسى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1017-item2">
                     <locus from="22r" to="47v">ff. 22r-47v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_12392936">Nāṣir al-Dīn al-Ṭūsī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_12392936">ناصر طوسى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1446">Awṣāf al-ashraf</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Treatise abridging the <title>Akhlāq-i Nāṣirī</title> on Sufism and ethics by the same author, <persName key="person_12392936" role="aut">Nāṣir al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad ibn Ḥasan al-Ṭūsī</persName> (d. 672/1273-4), adapted at the suggestion on the Ilkhanid courtier, <persName key="person_f7086" role="pat">Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad al-Juvaynī</persName>. 

                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into six sections termed bāb listed in the introduction. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
